# Session Affinity

```yaml
sessionAffinity: None
```

Controls whether client requests are always sent to the same Pod.

### None

Requests are distributed across all available Pods.

Example:

```
Client
   │
   ▼
LoadBalancer
   │
 ┌─┴───────────────┐
 ▼                 ▼
Pod-1           Pod-2
```

This provides better load balancing.

---

## sessionAffinityConfig

```yaml
sessionAffinityConfig:
  clientIP:
    timeoutSeconds: 10800
```

This configuration is only used when:

```yaml
sessionAffinity: ClientIP
```

Since your configuration uses:

```yaml
sessionAffinity: None
```

this section is **ignored** by Kubernetes.

If you want sticky sessions, you would configure:

```yaml
sessionAffinity: ClientIP
```

Then a client would continue communicating with the same Pod for **10,800 seconds (3 hours)**.

---

# Ports

```yaml
ports:
```

Defines how traffic reaches the application.

---

## name

```yaml
name: e-track-app-svc
```

A friendly name for the Service port.

Useful when exposing multiple ports.

---

## port

```yaml
port: 8080
```

The port exposed by the Service.

Users connect to:

```
http://<External-IP>:8080
```

---

## targetPort

```yaml
targetPort: 8080
```

The port on which the Spring Boot container is listening.

You verified this using:

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod> -- netstat -tln
```

Output:

```
0.0.0.0:8080 LISTEN
```

Traffic flow:

```
User
   │
http://34.xxx.xxx.xxx:8080
   │
   ▼
LoadBalancer Service
   │
   ▼
Pod:8080
```

