# Summary

| Field | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `apiVersion: v1` | Uses the Kubernetes Core API |
| `kind: Service` | Creates a Service resource |
| `metadata.name` | Service name (`e-track-app-svc`) |
| `namespace` | Creates the Service in the `e-track-dev` namespace |
| `selector` | Routes traffic to Pods labeled `app: e-track-app` |
| `type: LoadBalancer` | Creates a Google Cloud external Load Balancer with a public IP |
| `sessionAffinity: None` | Distributes requests across all Pods |
| `sessionAffinityConfig` | Ignored because session affinity is disabled |
| `port: 8080` | Port exposed by the Service |
| `targetPort: 8080` | Port on which the Spring Boot container listens |
| **Purpose** | Exposes the Spring Boot application to the internet through a Google Cloud Load Balancer, distributing incoming traffic across all running application Pods. |